Instructions: We have a conference room within a co-working office space called Circuit Launch, located on the second floor. If you arrive early, just have a seat on the leather couches while waiting for your next session! 

Don't forget to bring a valid ID for live scan fingerprinting. If you haven't uploaded your registration or proof of insurance, please bring those as well.

The HopSkipDrive Team

items.description:
Hello, and thank you for signing up for this event. 

Our new participants had been working on this document 

Our amazing volunteers could help them with:

  • Understanding Git and Github

  • Data types and Variables on JS

  • Strings use and factoring on JS

  • Working with functions in JS


We will use this zoom link:   https://zoom.us/j/95344023411

Introduction:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1v54bB6ntRovJaGx-7SyFyE3aBJ3wQJMg9RvAOt5yqsk/edit

-Roadmap on Monday.com (always changing as needed—be open, the times are suggested but it's up to you to stay on schedule and complete everything)
-Stand-ups on Zoom
-Pairing assigned every day in the #pairs channel by SEAM (your matched pair is who you should work with on daily deliverables and check in with about your code challenge solutions)
-How homework includes whatever you don't complete (due the next morning)
-Lunch is usually 12-1 unless otherwise specified
-Wrap-up is about an hour starting at 4 pm
-Retros (reviewing how things went for the week) are 30 minutes at 4:30 on Fridays
-The weekly survey should be done right after retro and the wrap-up
-Volunteers come in at times indicated on the Teamup calendar (https://teamup.com/ksnmth2atqw3zbbqrz)
-We'll be starting the day leads program next week (you'll cover an outline later this week and assignments will be in the roadmap)
-Attendance being tracked (should work out being absent/late/tardy with your SEAM)
-Needing approval for absences
-Making open-source changes to the /curriculum repo
-Your first month is your time to work really hard and prove yourselves
-Pep talk—tough love | Prework Assessment |
-Icebreaker | names | pronouns | fun fact about yourself
